<hr /><div class="frontNewsItem odd"><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050311095006/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/693"><img src="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050311095006im_/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/image.php?id=news_693_img&amp;maxw=120&amp;maxh=120&amp;corners=10&amp;edge=1&amp;checksum=ff674684a84d06f1c7da2ec9dd94646b&amp;fn=fn.png" alt="Raul Kripalani, Sarah Deane, Matt Sharifi" title="Raul Kripalani, Sarah Deane, Matt Sharifi (Copyright: Joyce Lewis)" border="0" width="120" height="84" class="thumbnail" /></a><h3><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050311095006/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/693">Microsoft Gen ’05 student event tour hits Southampton</a></h3><p>Microsoft student partners, 2nd year ECS Computer Science students Sarah Deane (centre) and Matt Sharifi (right, with ECS student Raul Kripalani) are helping out today (Wednesday) at the Microsoft Gen ’05 student technology roadshow. The roadshow, which is visiting Southampton for the first time, gives students the opportunity to see a multitude of new products and technologies in action. Over 500 students have so far visited Gen '05 in the West Building of the University Students' Union. Lectures and demonstrations run throughout the day until 5 pm.</p></div><div class="frontNewsItem even"><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050311095006/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/692"><img src="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050311095006im_/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/image.php?id=news_692_img&amp;maxw=120&amp;maxh=120&amp;corners=10&amp;edge=1&amp;checksum=4e8efa7ba95bd14184091b501bc639cc&amp;fn=fn.png" alt="Professor Nigel Shadbolt" title="Professor Nigel Shadbolt (Copyright: Steve Shrimpton)" border="0" width="93" height="120" class="thumbnail" /></a><h3><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050311095006/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/692">AI expert calls for e-defence for the UK</a></h3><p>The need for the UK military to develop e-defence so that it can compete with the rest of the world will be highlighted by Professor Nigel Shadbolt next week. His call will be made when he delivers the British Computer Society/Royal Signals Institution annual lecture on 'Web Intelligence' at the National Army Museum, London, on Wednesday 9 March. Professor Shadbolt, who is Professor of Artificial Intelligence at the School of Electronics and Computer Science, will focus on how Artificial Intelligence is being woven into the World Wide Web and review how these developments are likely to shape future military capabilities.</p><p></p></div><hr /><div class="frontNewsItem odd"><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050311095006/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/691"><img src="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050311095006im_/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/image.php?id=news_691_img&amp;maxw=120&amp;maxh=120&amp;corners=10&amp;edge=1&amp;checksum=52247ea2db1b9d109149c0555922f46b&amp;fn=fn.png" alt="Andy Livingstone and Lady Lloyd" title="Andy Livingstone and Lady Lloyd (Copyright: IEE)" border="0" width="80" height="120" class="thumbnail" /></a><h3><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050311095006/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/691">ECS student wins prestigious national award</a></h3><p>This year’s prestigious Lord Lloyd of Kilgerran Memorial Prize for undergraduate achievement has been awarded to Andrew Livingstone, a third-year MEng Electronics student in the School of Electronics and Computer Science. The annual Prize is intended to recognize outstanding national excellence in mobile radio communications and is administered by the Institution of Electrical Engineers. Andy received the award from Lady Lloyd at a formal prizegiving held yesterday at the IEE headquarters in London.</p><p></p></div><div class="frontNewsItem even"><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050311095006/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/689"><img src="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050311095006im_/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/image.php?id=news_689_img&amp;maxw=120&amp;maxh=120&amp;corners=10&amp;edge=1&amp;checksum=8c9300e28455e5c63ed46670e50b133d&amp;fn=fn.png" alt="IEEE logo" title="IEEE logo" border="0" width="120" height="36" class="thumbnail" /></a><h3><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050311095006/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/689">New ECS student branch of IEEE launches with talk by Lajos Hanzo</a></h3><p>A new student branch of the IEEE (Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers) has been established in the School of Electronics and Computer Science. The new student branch will be launched by a seminar given by Professor Lajos Hanzo, himself a Fellow of the IEEE, on Wireless Media Communications. The seminar takes place on Tuesday 1 March at 5.30 pm in Zepler Building, Seminar Room 1.</p></div><p class="clearBoth"><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050311095006/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/">More News</a></p><br style="clear: both;" />
